<div id="banner">
	<h1>War Tax</h1>
</div>

<div class="content">
<p>I had a dream that the president announced a war tax. It was a small tax, he said, about enough to purchase a rifle. And you didn&#8217;t have to pay it if you sent a reason why to the president. (But that was just a formaility, he didn&#8217;t actually read them.)</p>

<p>I thought this would be a great way to register opposition to the war: flood the White House with these letters. I also wanted to ask Raph if Quakers could pay the tax.</p>

<p class="posted">posted January 27, 2003 07:50 AM (<a class="category" href="http://www.aaronsw.com/weblog/cat_dreams">Dreams</a>)  <a href="000824" rel="bookmark">#</a></p>
</div>

